		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The site is in chinese</div><br />Japanese, actually.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">so even if my computer somehow manage to show chinese characters</div>
<br />Are you getting squares in place of the characters? If you're using XP, you can pick "Regional and Language Options" from the control panel, go to the "Languages" tab and select "Instal files for East Asian languages". You'll need your Windows CD. When it's done you'll be able to read (uh, I mean... "see") japanese, chinese, korean, and god knows what else.
<br />
<br />After you installed the files, you can also include japanese as an input language in your computer, so you can directly write katakana, hiragana and kanji. I don't know if it's as easy with the other languages.

		

